  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Cameroon Street Children SOS</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Douala, Cameroon&apos;s largest city is home to hundreds of children and young people living on its streets. All are vulnerable to abuse and exploitation. Many thousands more are vulnerable to making a living from the streets. Widows&apos; lack of inheritance rights is known to be a particular reason for destitution and a direct cause of children living on the street. This project will run a drop-in centre that will meet the immediate and longer term health, education and recreation needs of street children. Sport, including football, will feature as an important recreational activity.  Older children will be given vocational training, and apprenticeships with local businesses. Where necessary, the project will get birth certificates for children. This means they can get identity cards, and so have a right to health and education services, as well as broader citizenship rights. The project will get more children off the street, into education, and make sure the government does more to meet the needs of this very vulnerable group.</narrative>
  </description>
